# Presentation of article and subject
  - Proof of Conecpt or Get the Fuck Out issue 8 - Deniable Backdoors Using Compiler Bugs.
  - Taking advantage of compiler bugs that causes miscompilations.

# Exploiting CLANG/LLVM to compile bad sudo
  - CLANG/LLVM
  - Introduce bug
  - DEMO: Simplebug
  - Explaining sudo
  - Describe exploit

# DEMO: sudo
  - Create user:              sudo useradd bob
  - Change user:              su bob; whoami
  - Who has sudo permissions: sudo less /etc/sudoers
  - Show groups:              groups
  - Shadow:                   cat /etc/shadow
  - Sudo shadow:              sudo cat /etc/shadow
  - Badsudo shadow:           ./sudo cat /etc/shadow

